Run either main.py or waypoint.py depending on what you want

You need to have python (3.11 and 3.14 works, most versions around those should work) import dynamixel sdk, ultralytics (YOLO), inputs (for gamepad) opencv (cv2) 

You can delete the cup data set and trainer if you want

Setup python:
Google python 3.14 and use that, it can work for lower version too. I am not sure about higher ones

how to setup dynamixel sdk:
Official instructions: https://emanual.robotis.com/docs/en/software/dynamixel/dynamixel_sdk/overview/#dynamixel-sdk

download it: git clone https://github.com/ROBOTIS-GIT/DynamixelSDK.git
then add it to your python by:
1. go to the dynamixel sdk folder you just downloaded and navigate to the python folder via file explorer and open the command promt via typing cmd in the file navigator
2. Use this command if on windows:
pip install .
3. Check the motor.py file in this project and see if import dynamixel line is no longer marked

how to setup cv2:
Open the terminal/command promt and use this line:
pip install opencv-python

how to setup YOLO:
Official instructions: https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics

Download it via command promt/terminal:
pip install ultralytics

Check if its working by checking the Camera.py file and if import ultralytics is marked then:
Download Microsoft Visual C++ Redistributable. Use the one marked X64
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/windows/latest-supported-vc-redist?view=msvc-170
Once its installed restart computer and then the ultralytics import should be fixed

for gamepad inputs run this line in terminal/command promt
pip install inputs